1
00:00:01,268 --> 00:00:04,138
Boy: Ah, looks like
new pages are appearing.

2
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:07,174
I wonder what’ll happen next.

3
00:00:07,207 --> 00:00:11,378
The brothers delayed their trip
and took a bus four hours later,

4
00:00:11,411 --> 00:00:16,049
so they managed to avoid getting
into an accident. Yippee!

5
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,018
What adventures
awaited them now?

6
00:00:18,051 --> 00:00:20,320
Once in aswan,
they made their discovery.

7
00:00:20,354 --> 00:00:21,555
"Oh. There they are,

8
00:00:21,588 --> 00:00:23,657
the five bad guys,"
cried the brothers.

9
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:26,126
But the brothers wondered,

10
00:00:26,159 --> 00:00:27,527
"what could they
be talking about?"

11
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:30,130
The bad guys seemed so worried.

12
00:00:30,164 --> 00:00:33,300
Man: Hmm. I think that’s them.

13
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:36,403
Boy: Little did they know
they had drunk poison tea.

14
00:00:36,436 --> 00:00:37,404
( Gulps )

15
00:00:37,437 --> 00:00:39,005
( Chuckles )

16
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,974
Brother, check it out.

17
00:00:41,008 --> 00:00:42,543
Earth to big bro?

18
00:00:42,576 --> 00:00:44,144
Man: Huh?

19
00:00:46,079 --> 00:00:47,581
Huh?

20
00:00:47,614 --> 00:00:49,583
( Chuckles )

21
00:00:49,616 --> 00:00:52,319
So I just have to poison them.

22
00:00:52,352 --> 00:00:53,753
( Chuckles )

23
00:00:56,456 --> 00:00:58,158
Listen, little bro,

24
00:00:58,192 --> 00:01:00,294
you and I are practically
invincible together.

25
00:01:00,327 --> 00:01:03,297
Between your
clairvoyant comic stand

26
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:06,600
and my face stand’s
transformative ability,

27
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:09,102
no one can get in our way!

28
00:01:10,537 --> 00:01:13,140
Those guys are as good as dead.

29
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:16,009
We possess the cards known
as thoth, the god of writing,

30
00:01:16,043 --> 00:01:18,112
and khnum, god of creation,

31
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:21,782
and together we are
the bestest brothers ever!

32
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:23,817
♪

33
00:01:26,053 --> 00:01:28,055
( Singing in Japanese )

34
00:01:47,574 --> 00:01:49,576
♪

35
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:51,445
( Man humming a tune )

36
00:01:51,478 --> 00:01:52,679
( Gags )

37
00:01:54,214 --> 00:01:56,249
♪

38
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:04,458
Zenyatta: It’s here
in this cafe.

39
00:02:04,491 --> 00:02:07,094
( Slurps ) Right at that table.

40
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,630
That’s where those guys
will drink their poison tea.

41
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:13,667
Mondatta: Yeah, my stand,
thoth, the god of writing,

42
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,569
has never been wrong
about anything

43
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:17,237
when it comes to predictions.

44
00:02:17,271 --> 00:02:19,273
( Laughing )

45
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:28,849
Polnareff: Well,
are they gonna pull through?

46
00:02:28,882 --> 00:02:31,551
Joseph: Luckily, avdol’s
major arteries weren’t damaged,

47
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:33,821
so he’ll probably
be released by tomorrow.

48
00:02:33,854 --> 00:02:35,589
But, kakyoin, on the other hand,

49
00:02:35,622 --> 00:02:37,791
has serious injuries
that need to be treated.

50
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,626
There’s a chance
he could go blind.

51
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:40,794
Polnareff: That’s a raw deal.

52
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:42,562
Joseph: I hate to say it,

53
00:02:42,596 --> 00:02:44,565
but if his condition
doesn’t improve soon,

54
00:02:44,598 --> 00:02:46,533
we might have
to leave him behind.

55
00:02:48,468 --> 00:02:49,569
Polnareff: Hmm?

56
00:02:49,603 --> 00:02:51,572
♪

57
00:02:51,605 --> 00:02:54,341
Hey, since there are
so many cafes nearby,

58
00:02:54,374 --> 00:02:55,775
how ’bout we
get ourselves a drink?

59
00:02:55,809 --> 00:02:56,810
Joseph: That’s a great idea.

60
00:02:56,844 --> 00:02:58,446
Which one did you have in mind?

61
00:02:58,478 --> 00:02:59,479
Polnareff: Hmm.

62
00:03:03,817 --> 00:03:07,821
There you have it.
The cigarette has spoken.

63
00:03:07,855 --> 00:03:09,690
( Sighs )

64
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:11,258
Zenyatta: Hello, there.

65
00:03:12,693 --> 00:03:16,730
Tell me, sirs,
how may I be of service?

66
00:03:16,763 --> 00:03:19,232
Polnareff: Well,
tea sounds good right about now.

67
00:03:19,266 --> 00:03:20,334
Jotaro: Same.

68
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:22,269
Zenyatta: Right, so three teas.

69
00:03:22,302 --> 00:03:23,503
Be back in a jiffy.

70
00:03:24,905 --> 00:03:27,408
Joseph: Actually, scratch
that order, if you would.

71
00:03:27,441 --> 00:03:29,243
- Polnareff: Huh?
- Joseph: Hear me out.

72
00:03:29,276 --> 00:03:30,744
We’re in enemy territory here.

73
00:03:30,777 --> 00:03:32,379
This is dio’s dominion,

74
00:03:32,412 --> 00:03:34,781
and since we don’t know
when enemies will attack,

75
00:03:34,815 --> 00:03:36,250
we have to be cautious.

76
00:03:36,283 --> 00:03:38,452
If we let our guard down
even for a second,

77
00:03:38,485 --> 00:03:39,486
someone could poison us.

78
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,222
From this point on,

79
00:03:41,255 --> 00:03:43,224
we’re only drinking
from bottles and cans.

80
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:45,359
Polnareff: Come on.
Are you serious?

81
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,328
Joseph: Completely. Hey, there,
you can forget the tea,

82
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:50,531
- and bring us colas instead.
- Zenyatta: Huh?

83
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:52,433
Cola?!

84
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:55,235
Jotaro: That’s right.
Something wrong?

85
00:03:55,269 --> 00:03:57,805
Zenyatta: Not at all.
Okay, three colas coming up.

86
00:03:57,838 --> 00:03:59,239
Joseph: Hmm?

87
00:03:59,273 --> 00:04:00,875
Zenyatta: I’ll just
go and grab them.

88
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:03,344
Joseph: Oh, by the way,
if you don’t mind,

89
00:04:03,377 --> 00:04:05,346
we’ll open them ourselves,
and to make sure

90
00:04:05,379 --> 00:04:07,248
we’re not falling victim
to any funny business,

91
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:08,783
give us the third,
fourth, and fifth ones

92
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:10,183
from the far-right side.

93
00:04:10,217 --> 00:04:12,519
Zenyatta: Now they want
unopened colas?

94
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:15,523
How am I supposed
to put poison in those?

95
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:18,192
Was the prediction wrong?
No, that can’t be it.

96
00:04:18,225 --> 00:04:19,893
My brother’s comic
is always right.

97
00:04:19,927 --> 00:04:22,496
Damn it.
I’ve got to get it together.

98
00:04:22,529 --> 00:04:23,864
I just have to believe.

99
00:04:23,897 --> 00:04:26,500
If I don’t have absolute faith
in little bro,

100
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:27,934
we won’t stand a chance.

101
00:04:27,968 --> 00:04:30,871
Mondatta: Yes, my predictions
are foolproof, brother.

102
00:04:30,904 --> 00:04:32,339
Man: You in the apron,

103
00:04:32,372 --> 00:04:34,641
is this warm cola
your idea of a cold drink?

104
00:04:34,675 --> 00:04:36,744
You must assume i’m
a real halfwit or something

105
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:39,313
to think i’d pay
for this excuse of a beverage.

106
00:04:39,346 --> 00:04:41,248
Joseph: Wait. What?
The cola’s really not cold?

107
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:42,415
Zenyatta:
Sorry about the hassle.

108
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,384
The fridge is down, so...

109
00:04:44,418 --> 00:04:46,854
Polnareff: Hey, don’t you think
you’re being a little paranoid?

110
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:48,489
Let’s say,
for the sake of argument,

111
00:04:48,522 --> 00:04:50,758
that guy was our enemy
and he was trying his damnedest

112
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,827
to slip a little poison
into our drinks.

113
00:04:53,861 --> 00:04:56,497
How would he have known
to come to this exact cafe?

114
00:04:56,530 --> 00:04:59,366
I mean, this city’s not lacking
in places to get a drink,

115
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,967
and I chose this one on a whim.

116
00:05:01,001 --> 00:05:02,970
I’d understand
if this were the only cafe,

117
00:05:03,003 --> 00:05:04,738
but there are tons of ’em.

118
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:07,240
Joseph: My point is we can’t
be too careful around here.

119
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:08,776
Polnareff: Well,
if you’re that worried,

120
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:09,977
let’s go somewhere else then,

121
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:11,845
maybe the place
across the street?

122
00:05:11,879 --> 00:05:13,547
Joseph: Mm.

123
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,881
- ( Man yells )
- Man #2: Fire!

124
00:05:14,915 --> 00:05:17,651
Man #1: What do I do?
My cafe is on fire!

125
00:05:17,684 --> 00:05:18,952
( Wails )

126
00:05:18,986 --> 00:05:21,422
Some fool left
a burning cigarette in the road,

127
00:05:21,455 --> 00:05:23,757
- and it ignited the trash.
- Polnareff: Uh, oh ,boy.

128
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:25,258
Joseph: You know what?

129
00:05:25,292 --> 00:05:26,860
I think we’ll take
those teas after all.

130
00:05:26,894 --> 00:05:28,596
( Zenyatta laughs )

131
00:05:28,629 --> 00:05:31,532
Mondatta: Yes, we did it.

132
00:05:31,565 --> 00:05:33,934
Polnareff: Ah, zut alors.

133
00:05:33,967 --> 00:05:36,736
What kind of jerk would toss
a lit cigarette near the trash?

134
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:38,338
Really,
the nerve of some people.

135
00:05:38,372 --> 00:05:41,575
♪

136
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:47,681
Zenyatta: Finally,
they’re drinking it.

137
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:52,085
Mondatta: Drink it. Drink it.
Drink it until it’s gone.

138
00:05:53,654 --> 00:05:55,389
( Brothers laugh )
They drank it!

139
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:58,358
( Woman screams )
A dog just took my cake.

140
00:05:58,392 --> 00:06:00,861
Man: Who the hell brought
a mangy mutt to a freakin’ cafe?

141
00:06:04,998 --> 00:06:06,800
Men: Iggy.

142
00:06:06,834 --> 00:06:08,402
Woman: Whose dog is this?!

143
00:06:08,435 --> 00:06:10,003
Man: Will somebody please
get this dog outta here?!

144
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:11,405
( Brothers gulp )

145
00:06:11,438 --> 00:06:12,406
( Iggy barks )

146
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:13,807
Joseph: Damn it, iggy!

147
00:06:13,841 --> 00:06:17,912
Polnareff: Get back here,
you fleabag!

148
00:06:17,945 --> 00:06:19,547
Zenyatta: Damn it!

149
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:22,083
They were just
about to swallow the poison.

150
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:23,617
Dumb mutt.

151
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:26,019
So what the hell’s
supposed to happen next?

152
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:29,089
Mondatta: Well, thing is
the page hasn’t appeared yet.

153
00:06:29,122 --> 00:06:33,693
Also, while off, it wasn’t
entirely wrong. Be patient.

154
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:36,964
Thoth only has the ability
to see the near future,

155
00:06:36,997 --> 00:06:38,432
so Patience is key.

156
00:06:38,465 --> 00:06:39,599
Zenyatta: Next time, then.

157
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:41,335
When the next premonition
is revealed,

158
00:06:41,368 --> 00:06:42,836
we’ll use it to destroy them.

159
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:45,740
This is what we
were meant to do.

160
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:49,442
Together, we’re
the bestest brothers ever, baby.

161
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:52,479
"’we failed to kill them
because of that darn dog.’"

162
00:06:52,513 --> 00:06:54,749
mondatta: "’we were so close,’
fumed the brothers.

163
00:06:54,781 --> 00:06:57,384
"The brothers were
beside themselves with anger,

164
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:58,919
"’cause their plan failed,

165
00:06:58,952 --> 00:07:00,887
"but the brothers
didn’t give up,

166
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:04,758
"and soon they decided to follow
the three guys and their dog.

167
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:06,026
"While following them,

168
00:07:06,059 --> 00:07:08,595
they met a man who had
a very annoying face,

169
00:07:08,629 --> 00:07:11,432
"the kind of face that was
just begging to be hit.

170
00:07:11,465 --> 00:07:14,468
In fact, it was the kind
of face the brothers hated."

171
00:07:14,501 --> 00:07:17,004
Zenyatta: I must have hated
that face in a past life,

172
00:07:17,037 --> 00:07:20,007
and a face like that
deserves a knuckle sandwich.

173
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,843
Mondatta: "Even though
he was a perfectly nice man,

174
00:07:22,876 --> 00:07:24,578
big bro punched him anyway."

175
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:25,612
( Man groans )

176
00:07:25,646 --> 00:07:27,681
( Gasps )

177
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:30,717
Mondatta: "Thus, the man
with the bad face ran away"...

178
00:07:30,751 --> 00:07:32,419
( Man wails )

179
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,920
Mondatta:
"But fortunately for them,

180
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:36,056
"he dropped
a wallet full of money.

181
00:07:36,089 --> 00:07:39,492
"’yay. We’re rich.
Whoopee!’ cried mondatta."

182
00:07:39,526 --> 00:07:41,762
( Zenyatta laughs )
What a dumb-ass.

183
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:45,499
Mondatta: Yeah, thanks to that
smarmy-faced fool, we’re rich.

184
00:07:45,532 --> 00:07:47,501
( Laughs )

185
00:07:47,534 --> 00:07:50,070
Huh? Hey, brother, check it out.

186
00:07:50,103 --> 00:07:52,706
- The new page is coming.
- Zenyatta: Oh.

187
00:07:52,739 --> 00:07:55,875
Mondatta: "The brothers
continued their pursuit.

188
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:59,446
"The bad guys got in their car
and hurried over to the hospital

189
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,614
"to check on their friends
avdol and kakyoin.

190
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,818
"But they had no idea
zenyatta had made a bomb,

191
00:08:04,852 --> 00:08:07,688
"placed it an orange,
and planted it in the car.

192
00:08:07,721 --> 00:08:10,157
"Jotaro was blown
into a million pieces.

193
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:11,758
"His head was split in two,

194
00:08:11,792 --> 00:08:14,628
and his blood
was splattered everywhere!"

195
00:08:14,661 --> 00:08:16,596
L-l-l-look how clearly

196
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:18,499
the pictures
in the comic came in.

197
00:08:18,532 --> 00:08:20,167
Zenyatta: I see!

198
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:24,504
♪

199
00:08:24,538 --> 00:08:26,540
( Zenyatta humming a tune )

200
00:08:35,148 --> 00:08:37,150
( Ticking )

201
00:08:38,151 --> 00:08:40,320
( Mondatta laughing )

202
00:08:45,626 --> 00:08:49,363
It’s true that my stand, thoth,
can only see the near future,

203
00:08:49,396 --> 00:08:53,133
and most would see that
as a disadvantage, but--heh--

204
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:56,404
once the prediction has been
printed, it can’t be changed,

205
00:08:56,436 --> 00:08:58,672
no matter what anybody does,
not ever.

206
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:01,508
Zenyatta: We’re gonna
blow jotaro to smithereens.

207
00:09:01,542 --> 00:09:03,177
The bomb will detonate

208
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:06,246
three seconds after he sticks
his finger in to peel it.

209
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:08,249
It’s destiny.

210
00:09:08,282 --> 00:09:11,285
( Chuckles )

211
00:09:11,318 --> 00:09:12,519
This is the end.

212
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:14,722
There’s no way out.

213
00:09:14,755 --> 00:09:15,923
Joseph: Hmm?

214
00:09:15,956 --> 00:09:17,825
Polnareff: Who the hell
is in our car?!

215
00:09:17,858 --> 00:09:19,426
Do you recognize this bozo?

216
00:09:19,459 --> 00:09:21,895
- Joseph: What? Isn’t it jotaro?
- Polnareff: No.

217
00:09:21,929 --> 00:09:24,532
Jotaro said he was
going straight to the hospital.

218
00:09:24,565 --> 00:09:25,666
- Be careful.
- Zenyatta: Damn it.

219
00:09:25,699 --> 00:09:27,267
Joseph: Don’t let him get away!

220
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:28,435
Mondatta:
You’ve gotta be kidding.

221
00:09:28,468 --> 00:09:29,803
It’s joestar and polnareff.

222
00:09:29,837 --> 00:09:31,839
Polnareff: Whoever you are,
come out this instant!

223
00:09:31,872 --> 00:09:33,807
Joseph: What he said!
Out of the car!

224
00:09:33,841 --> 00:09:35,176
( Both gasp )

225
00:09:35,209 --> 00:09:36,210
Polnareff: Quit your stalling,

226
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:37,611
and get out of there already!

227
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:38,778
Joseph: Make it snappy.

228
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:44,584
Zenyatta: Hey, hey,
what’s the matter with you two?

229
00:09:44,618 --> 00:09:47,187
It was me. Couldn’t you tell?

230
00:09:47,221 --> 00:09:48,489
- Polnareff: Oh.
- Joseph: Oh,

231
00:09:48,522 --> 00:09:50,591
so it was you, jotaro.

232
00:09:50,624 --> 00:09:52,593
( Zenyatta chuckles )

233
00:09:52,626 --> 00:09:56,497
My stand, khnum, gives me
the power of transformation.

234
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:59,867
I can alter my height, weight,
and scent however I see fit.

235
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:03,203
I even used my hair
to recreate this hat.

236
00:10:03,237 --> 00:10:05,573
Polnareff: Wait. I don’t get it.
Last I heard,

237
00:10:05,606 --> 00:10:07,842
you said you were going to head
straight for the hospital.

238
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,710
Zenyatta: Huh? I did?

239
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:11,678
Ah, the hospital.

240
00:10:11,712 --> 00:10:14,782
I forgot something,
so I decided to come and get it.

241
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:17,251
Oh, that’s right.
I left my wallet in the car.

242
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:18,452
- Good grief.
- Joseph: Hmm.

243
00:10:18,485 --> 00:10:21,355
Jotaro,
where’s your school uniform?

244
00:10:21,388 --> 00:10:22,623
Zenyatta: Uh, uniform?

245
00:10:22,656 --> 00:10:23,891
What’s he talking about?

246
00:10:23,924 --> 00:10:25,292
What school uniform?

247
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:26,693
Polnareff:
Nothin’ personal, friend,

248
00:10:26,727 --> 00:10:29,530
but that’s not really
a good look on you. Heh.

249
00:10:29,563 --> 00:10:32,366
Zenyatta: Uh, ah, my outfit.

250
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:33,767
I mean uniform.

251
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:36,536
Well, it’s actually
at the dry cleaners.

252
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:38,338
I took it in for a wash,

253
00:10:38,372 --> 00:10:40,474
but then I realized
I didn’t have any money.

254
00:10:40,507 --> 00:10:43,810
Yeah, that’ll convince them.
I’m in the clear.

255
00:10:43,844 --> 00:10:46,480
Polnareff: That so?
All right then.

256
00:10:46,513 --> 00:10:49,716
You can go ahead and
hop in the car. Time to go.

257
00:10:50,751 --> 00:10:52,286
Zenyatta: Huh?

258
00:10:52,319 --> 00:10:53,787
Mondatta: Oh, no, not the car.

259
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,855
Then, that would mean.

260
00:10:55,889 --> 00:10:57,657
Zenyatta: No, i-it can’t be.

261
00:10:57,691 --> 00:10:59,793
If I get into the car
with this face,

262
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:02,762
that means the real jotaro won’t
be the one getting blown up.

263
00:11:02,796 --> 00:11:05,832
Instead, it’ll be me!

264
00:11:05,866 --> 00:11:07,034
Shit.

265
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:08,936
You know,
it’s a beautiful day out,

266
00:11:08,969 --> 00:11:10,671
so I think i’ll go ahead
and walk--

267
00:11:10,704 --> 00:11:11,838
polnareff: We don’t have time

268
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:13,440
to wait for you
to walk there, jotaro.

269
00:11:13,473 --> 00:11:14,774
Things’ll go a lot faster

270
00:11:14,808 --> 00:11:17,411
if you just get in the car
and ride over with us.

271
00:11:17,444 --> 00:11:20,681
Mondatta: Brother, you have
to get out of there now!

272
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:22,783
( Wails )

273
00:11:22,816 --> 00:11:25,052
Zenyatta: Crap, this is bad.

274
00:11:25,085 --> 00:11:27,621
I’ve got to undo
my jotaro disguise

275
00:11:27,654 --> 00:11:30,457
before it’s too late.
If I don’t,

276
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:33,593
i’ll be the one who gets
blown to bits instead!

277
00:11:34,661 --> 00:11:35,629
That’s it.

278
00:11:35,662 --> 00:11:37,464
I just need to throw it away.

279
00:11:37,498 --> 00:11:39,567
I’ll covertly
get rid of this one

280
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,735
and put another one
in the car later

281
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:43,436
so it can blow up
the real jotaro,

282
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:45,706
thereby saving my ass.

283
00:11:47,407 --> 00:11:48,675
I did it.

284
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:50,711
( Sighs ) What a relief.

285
00:11:50,744 --> 00:11:52,412
I’m safe.

286
00:11:52,446 --> 00:11:53,847
Polnareff: Hey,
what do you know? It’s iggy.

287
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:56,016
He’s chasing our car.

288
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:58,418
He’s got an orange in his mouth.

289
00:11:58,452 --> 00:11:59,887
Did you steal that, iggy?

290
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:02,423
It’ll make a nice gift
for kakyoin and avdol.

291
00:12:02,456 --> 00:12:03,557
Zenyatta: Hmm?

292
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:04,958
- ( Iggy grunts )
- Zenyatta: Wha--

293
00:12:04,992 --> 00:12:06,961
yow!

294
00:12:06,994 --> 00:12:09,463
Both: Come again?

295
00:12:09,496 --> 00:12:10,897
Joseph: Everything okay?

296
00:12:10,931 --> 00:12:13,333
Never thought i’d hear you
say something like that.

297
00:12:13,367 --> 00:12:15,936
Zenyatta: Oh, really?
That’s weird. "Yow"?

298
00:12:15,969 --> 00:12:17,070
You know, "yow."

299
00:12:17,104 --> 00:12:18,472
Actually, I was pointing out

300
00:12:18,505 --> 00:12:19,873
that there’s
a "cyow" over there.

301
00:12:19,907 --> 00:12:20,875
Polnareff: A cow?

302
00:12:20,908 --> 00:12:22,676
( Cow moos )

303
00:12:22,709 --> 00:12:24,578
Polnareff: Man,
you sure are acting

304
00:12:24,611 --> 00:12:26,012
pretty peculiar today, jotaro.

305
00:12:26,046 --> 00:12:28,115
You’re usually a lot cooler.

306
00:12:28,148 --> 00:12:30,884
I hate to say this,
but i’ve gotta wonder.

307
00:12:30,918 --> 00:12:34,855
You’re not really a fake,
are you, jotaro?

308
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:37,457
( Zenyatta stammers )

309
00:12:37,491 --> 00:12:39,693
Joseph: Hmm.

310
00:12:39,726 --> 00:12:42,395
( Iggy grumbles )

311
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:45,599
♪

312
00:12:45,632 --> 00:12:47,667
Zenyatta: G-good grief,
polnareff.

313
00:12:47,701 --> 00:12:49,836
What the hell are you
even talking about, man?

314
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:52,005
By the way,
are we at the hospital yet?

315
00:12:52,039 --> 00:12:54,742
( Chuckles )

316
00:12:57,945 --> 00:12:59,814
Polnareff: Hey, jotaro,
i’m super bored,

317
00:12:59,847 --> 00:13:02,083
so how about you show me
that trick again?

318
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:05,018
Zenyatta: Hmm. A trick?
Which one is that?

319
00:13:05,052 --> 00:13:06,520
What’s he talking about?

320
00:13:06,553 --> 00:13:09,122
Polnareff: The one
you taught me a while back.

321
00:13:09,156 --> 00:13:11,158
You know, this one here.

322
00:13:15,495 --> 00:13:18,465
Joseph: Hey, you’ve gotten a bit
better at that, polnareff.

323
00:13:18,499 --> 00:13:20,134
( Polnareff chuckles )

324
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:22,870
Zenyatta: Oh, that’s the trick
you were talking about.

325
00:13:22,903 --> 00:13:26,006
Thank goodness.
I know how to do that one.

326
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:28,441
It’s risky,
but I can pull it off.

327
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:30,510
Why didn’t you say so
from the beginning?

328
00:13:30,544 --> 00:13:31,645
That’s an easy one.

329
00:13:31,678 --> 00:13:33,146
Polnareff: All right.
In that case,

330
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:34,915
do the one
with five cigarettes, then.

331
00:13:34,948 --> 00:13:38,018
( Zenyatta gasps )
F-five cigarettes?

332
00:13:38,051 --> 00:13:40,020
Polnareff: Hurry it up already,
would you?

333
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,755
I wanna see the trick again.

334
00:13:41,788 --> 00:13:44,724
Zenyatta: Why is this
happening to me?

335
00:13:44,758 --> 00:13:48,762
Damn that jotaro, and damn
his stupid party tricks!

336
00:13:48,795 --> 00:13:51,097
But if I don’t
at least try to do it,

337
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:53,133
they’ll really think
something is up.

338
00:13:53,167 --> 00:13:56,971
They’re already becoming more
suspicious of me by the minute.

339
00:13:57,004 --> 00:13:59,507
And polnareff,
loathsome idiot that he is,

340
00:13:59,540 --> 00:14:01,976
is seconds away
from setting off the bomb.

341
00:14:02,009 --> 00:14:05,579
All right, fine. Damn it.

342
00:14:05,612 --> 00:14:07,781
I’ll do it!

343
00:14:07,814 --> 00:14:09,049
( Grunts )

344
00:14:09,082 --> 00:14:11,184
Have it your way.
Five cigarettes.

345
00:14:11,218 --> 00:14:15,989
♪

346
00:14:16,023 --> 00:14:17,224
( Joseph laughs )

347
00:14:17,257 --> 00:14:18,225
Polnareff: That’s the way.

348
00:14:18,258 --> 00:14:19,926
Now come on. Do the trick.

349
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,763
Zenyatta: All right,
it’s now or never.

350
00:14:22,796 --> 00:14:25,666
I’m gonna do it.
I’m gonna do the trick, damn it.

351
00:14:25,699 --> 00:14:27,734
Here goes nothing!

352
00:14:27,768 --> 00:14:29,903
( Stammering ) Hot.

353
00:14:29,937 --> 00:14:32,106
H-hot. Hot.

354
00:14:32,139 --> 00:14:34,141
I did it!

355
00:14:34,174 --> 00:14:37,010
Hot damn, I did it!

356
00:14:37,044 --> 00:14:39,547
Both: Ah!

357
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:41,849
Zenyatta: There.
Did you see that? I did it!

358
00:14:41,882 --> 00:14:44,685
A man can do anything
when his life is on the line.

359
00:14:44,718 --> 00:14:45,852
Polnareff: Here.

360
00:14:45,886 --> 00:14:47,654
Last time,
you did this super cool move

361
00:14:47,688 --> 00:14:49,623
where you drank
a bottle of juice

362
00:14:49,656 --> 00:14:50,891
without putting
the cigarettes out.

363
00:14:50,924 --> 00:14:52,926
( Zenyatta stammering )

364
00:14:55,796 --> 00:14:58,098
Polnareff: Come on. Drink up.

365
00:15:04,671 --> 00:15:06,072
( Zenyatta screams )

366
00:15:06,106 --> 00:15:07,708
Polnareff: Aw, you blew it!

367
00:15:07,741 --> 00:15:11,245
Joseph: Jotaro,
are you all right? Oh, my god!

368
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:14,748
Zenyatta: Brother! Brother!
Please, little bro,

369
00:15:14,781 --> 00:15:17,017
make that prediction
go away right now!

370
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:19,653
Tear up that page!

371
00:15:19,686 --> 00:15:22,689
Mondatta: Sorry, big bro, but
the prediction can’t be changed.

372
00:15:22,723 --> 00:15:25,025
Hurry, and go back
to your regular self.

373
00:15:25,058 --> 00:15:26,793
If you can undo the disguise,

374
00:15:26,827 --> 00:15:29,096
the real jotaro
will get blown up instead.

375
00:15:29,129 --> 00:15:30,864
I believe in you, brother.

376
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:35,235
Polnareff: Jotaro, I know
we’ve said this already,

377
00:15:35,269 --> 00:15:37,772
but you’re acting
really weird today.

378
00:15:37,804 --> 00:15:39,072
Zenyatta: It’s nothing.

379
00:15:39,106 --> 00:15:41,675
I just feel a little
under the weather is all.

380
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:43,977
Both: Hmm.

381
00:15:44,011 --> 00:15:45,980
♪

382
00:15:46,013 --> 00:15:47,548
Eh?

383
00:15:47,581 --> 00:15:49,783
Zenyatta: Crap.
This couldn’t get any worse.

384
00:15:49,816 --> 00:15:52,986
I know their type.
Since i’ve put them on guard,

385
00:15:53,020 --> 00:15:55,789
they’re gonna interrogate me
and realize i’m an imposter.

386
00:15:55,822 --> 00:15:58,158
If they figure me out,
they’ll kill me,

387
00:15:58,192 --> 00:15:59,894
and if I don’t undo my disguise,

388
00:15:59,927 --> 00:16:02,029
i’ll blow up
just like the prophecy said.

389
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:04,031
Ah?

390
00:16:04,064 --> 00:16:06,033
That’s it.
I’ll just pretend i’m sick

391
00:16:06,066 --> 00:16:08,268
and make them let me
out of the car

392
00:16:08,302 --> 00:16:10,237
to relieve myself. Brilliant.

393
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:12,672
Polnareff: Jotaro,
I couldn’t help but notice

394
00:16:12,706 --> 00:16:14,675
the way you’re
clasping your hands.

395
00:16:15,976 --> 00:16:17,778
Aha! Are you aware

396
00:16:17,811 --> 00:16:19,780
you’ve got your left thumb
on top of the others?!

397
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:20,947
Well, are you?!

398
00:16:20,981 --> 00:16:22,950
- ( Zenyatta gasps )
- Polnareff: Hmph!

399
00:16:22,983 --> 00:16:25,953
Zenyatta: Damn it.
I wasn’t prepared for this.

400
00:16:25,986 --> 00:16:28,088
Does jotaro have a weird tic
that causes him

401
00:16:28,121 --> 00:16:31,191
to clasp his hands
with his right thumb on top?

402
00:16:31,225 --> 00:16:33,194
Who even notices
something like that?

403
00:16:33,227 --> 00:16:34,962
What am I gonna do?

404
00:16:34,995 --> 00:16:36,196
( Polnareff laughs )

405
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:38,232
That just proves
beyond a shadow of a doubt

406
00:16:38,265 --> 00:16:40,200
that you were a woman
in a past life!

407
00:16:40,234 --> 00:16:43,604
And since, unlike you, I always
put my right thumb on top,

408
00:16:43,637 --> 00:16:46,106
it proves that I was a man
in my past life.

409
00:16:46,139 --> 00:16:47,641
Joseph: Wow, now how about that?

410
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:49,843
I always put my left thumb
on top, as well.

411
00:16:49,877 --> 00:16:51,345
Polnareff: Sorry, Mr. Joestar,

412
00:16:51,378 --> 00:16:53,981
but that proves you, too,
were a woman in a past life.

413
00:16:54,014 --> 00:16:56,116
Joseph: Says you.
How does it prove anything?

414
00:16:56,149 --> 00:16:59,019
How do thumbs factor
into reincarnation?

415
00:16:59,052 --> 00:17:00,754
That’s so stupid.

416
00:17:00,787 --> 00:17:03,657
- ( Both laughing )
- ( Zenyatta groaning )

417
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:08,162
Now I really do feel sick.

418
00:17:08,195 --> 00:17:12,332
These rabid lunatics
are driving me up the wall.

419
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:15,402
All right, i’ll tell them
i’ve got a stomachache.

420
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:17,370
Polnareff: Jotaro,
what do you say we find out

421
00:17:17,404 --> 00:17:19,640
which one of us can eat
an orange the fastest?

422
00:17:19,673 --> 00:17:21,041
Zenyatta: Say what?

423
00:17:21,074 --> 00:17:24,144
- ( Polnareff humming )
- Zenyatta: Hey, maybe you--

424
00:17:24,178 --> 00:17:26,847
stop it!
Don’t do that, you idiot!

425
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,014
Polnareff: Whoa there!

426
00:17:28,048 --> 00:17:29,983
What the hell
are you doing, jotaro?

427
00:17:30,017 --> 00:17:33,954
Joseph: What’s going on
with you today, jotaro?

428
00:17:33,987 --> 00:17:36,022
Zenyatta:
Oh, it’s nothing, guys.

429
00:17:36,056 --> 00:17:37,791
Joseph: But this
isn’t like you at all.

430
00:17:37,824 --> 00:17:39,192
Zenyatta: I just
don’t think it’s good

431
00:17:39,226 --> 00:17:40,728
for you to eat
that particular orange.

432
00:17:40,761 --> 00:17:42,096
Polnareff:
What’s the problem with it?

433
00:17:42,129 --> 00:17:44,131
Zenyatta: Well,
it’s obvious, isn’t it?

434
00:17:44,164 --> 00:17:46,767
Who knows where the heck
iggy found that thing?

435
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,736
For all we know, he could have
dug it out of the gutter.

436
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:50,904
You should eat a different one.

437
00:17:50,938 --> 00:17:52,139
Polnareff: Thanks for caring,

438
00:17:52,172 --> 00:17:53,440
but it doesn’t look
bruised or dirty,

439
00:17:53,473 --> 00:17:54,808
so I think i’ll be fine.

440
00:17:54,842 --> 00:17:55,810
I’ll eat this one,

441
00:17:55,843 --> 00:17:57,345
and you can have one of those.

442
00:17:57,377 --> 00:18:00,313
I can’t wait to see the look
on your face when I win.

443
00:18:00,347 --> 00:18:02,082
- Zenyatta: Ow! The pain!
- Both: Huh?!

444
00:18:02,115 --> 00:18:03,850
Polnareff: Hey, what’s wrong?

445
00:18:03,884 --> 00:18:06,820
Zenyatta: Please, stop the car.
I have to go to the bathroom.

446
00:18:06,854 --> 00:18:09,323
Come on. Stop the car! Hurry!

447
00:18:09,356 --> 00:18:11,892
Polnareff: Does your stomach
really hurt that bad?

448
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:14,795
( Zenyatta groans )
I can’t hold it anymore!

449
00:18:14,828 --> 00:18:17,864
Let me out! Let me out!
I’ll go behind that rock!

450
00:18:17,898 --> 00:18:20,000
Joseph: The hospital’s
right there. Just hang on.

451
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:22,302
Zenyatta: No, no,
go on ahead without me.

452
00:18:22,336 --> 00:18:24,772
I’ll catch up
once i’m done. Ohh!

453
00:18:24,805 --> 00:18:27,207
♪

454
00:18:27,241 --> 00:18:29,009
( Panting )

455
00:18:29,042 --> 00:18:31,044
Polnareff: Not so fast, jotaro.

456
00:18:31,078 --> 00:18:33,914
( Both groan )

457
00:18:33,947 --> 00:18:35,916
( Zenyatta gasping )

458
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:38,318
♪

459
00:18:38,352 --> 00:18:40,321
( Both groan )

460
00:18:42,823 --> 00:18:45,025
( Groaning )

461
00:18:45,058 --> 00:18:47,327
♪

462
00:18:50,964 --> 00:18:52,299
Polnareff: Take this. It’s--

463
00:18:52,332 --> 00:18:54,334
zenyatta: Yes!

464
00:18:54,368 --> 00:18:57,304
I did it!
I can’t believe I did it!

465
00:18:57,337 --> 00:19:01,908
I actually managed to get out
of that metal deathtrap alive!

466
00:19:01,942 --> 00:19:04,812
I’ll go behind that rock
and undo my disguise.

467
00:19:07,047 --> 00:19:08,782
Polnareff:
He brought up a good point.

468
00:19:08,815 --> 00:19:10,283
Who knows where iggy
found this orange?

469
00:19:10,317 --> 00:19:13,020
For all we know, it could have
been lying in the gutter.

470
00:19:13,053 --> 00:19:15,088
Do you wanna eat it?

471
00:19:15,122 --> 00:19:16,890
Joseph: Nah. You can toss it.

472
00:19:21,028 --> 00:19:22,796
Zenyatta: Success!

473
00:19:22,829 --> 00:19:25,965
Now I can use khnum’s powers
to transform back to normal.

474
00:19:25,999 --> 00:19:28,034
After that, they’ll get
what’s comin’ to ’em,

475
00:19:28,068 --> 00:19:31,004
and the zenyatta mondatta
brothers will have won again.

476
00:19:31,038 --> 00:19:32,373
( Laughs ) We win.

477
00:19:32,406 --> 00:19:34,308
( Laughs )

478
00:19:34,341 --> 00:19:37,277
Uh--( Gasps )

479
00:19:39,213 --> 00:19:41,082
( Ticking )

480
00:19:41,114 --> 00:19:43,950
Are you kidding me?!

481
00:19:46,587 --> 00:19:49,957
( Gasping )

482
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:52,326
Polnareff: Huh?
Did you hear that sound?

483
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:55,562
Joseph: Just forget it.
It was probably construction.

484
00:19:55,596 --> 00:19:57,798
( Sizzling )

485
00:19:57,831 --> 00:20:00,167
Mondatta: Oh!
Big bro, are you okay?

486
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,303
( Gasping ) Speak to me.

487
00:20:03,337 --> 00:20:05,139
Zenyatta: Hey, little bro.

488
00:20:05,172 --> 00:20:08,275
I think we lost this battle bad,
really bad.

489
00:20:08,308 --> 00:20:10,143
Mondatta: No, big brother.

490
00:20:10,177 --> 00:20:11,979
No, no way.

491
00:20:12,012 --> 00:20:15,215
Those wannabes haven’t beaten me
and my stand thoth yet.

492
00:20:15,249 --> 00:20:17,952
I-i’ll destroy them all,
brother,

493
00:20:17,985 --> 00:20:19,553
by myself, if I have to.

494
00:20:19,586 --> 00:20:22,155
- ( Zenyatta gasps )
- ( Mondatta growls )

495
00:20:22,189 --> 00:20:24,158
Zenyatta: No, don’t.

496
00:20:24,191 --> 00:20:26,160
Don’t do this, brother.

497
00:20:26,193 --> 00:20:29,897
These guys aren’t some rookies
you can push around. You’ll die.

498
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:33,901
Mondatta: I’ve already decided,
and I can beat them on my own.

499
00:20:33,934 --> 00:20:35,402
I know I can.

500
00:20:35,435 --> 00:20:37,971
Zenyatta:
You were always so shy.

501
00:20:38,005 --> 00:20:41,408
You’ve really grown up,
little bro.

502
00:20:41,441 --> 00:20:43,977
Mondatta:
I’m gonna kill ’em all.

503
00:20:44,011 --> 00:20:46,347
What does the book of thoth
say next?

504
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:48,415
Huh? ( Gasps )

505
00:20:48,448 --> 00:20:50,317
Man: This is them, all right!

506
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,885
They’re the ones who punched me

507
00:20:51,919 --> 00:20:53,988
and purloined my wallet
while they were at it.

508
00:20:54,021 --> 00:20:56,056
All right, men,
beat them to a bloody pulp,

509
00:20:56,089 --> 00:20:59,092
and i’ll make sure
you’re rewarded handsomely.

510
00:20:59,126 --> 00:21:00,094
( Men laugh )

511
00:21:00,127 --> 00:21:01,495
Zenyatta: It’s him again!

512
00:21:01,528 --> 00:21:02,896
Mondatta: I’m scared, brother!

513
00:21:02,930 --> 00:21:05,266
This doesn’t look good for us!

514
00:21:05,299 --> 00:21:09,203
"Despite his intense, yet
short-lived, burst of bravery,

515
00:21:09,236 --> 00:21:12,272
"mondatta would have to wait
a while to avenge his brother.

516
00:21:12,306 --> 00:21:14,175
"But try not to lose heart,
mondatta.

517
00:21:14,208 --> 00:21:18,446
Life is full of wonderful ups
and terrible downs."

518
00:21:20,214 --> 00:21:21,348
Polnareff: Huh?

519
00:21:21,381 --> 00:21:22,916
Joseph: Well,
if it isn’t jotaro.

520
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:23,918
Jotaro: Hmm?

521
00:21:23,951 --> 00:21:26,020
Hey, what took so long?

522
00:21:26,053 --> 00:21:28,122
Polnareff: Forget that.
How’d you take a dump

523
00:21:28,155 --> 00:21:30,491
- behind that rock so fast?
- Jotaro: Huh?

524
00:21:30,524 --> 00:21:32,593
Joseph: I can’t believe
you got here before us.

525
00:21:32,626 --> 00:21:35,129
You even found time
to go to the dry cleaners.

526
00:21:35,162 --> 00:21:37,197
Jotaro: What the hell
are you two talking about?

527
00:21:37,231 --> 00:21:38,432
- ( Siren blaring )
- Joseph: Hey,

528
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:39,433
it’s an ambulance.

529
00:21:39,466 --> 00:21:41,034
Jotaro: Someone must be hurt.

530
00:21:41,068 --> 00:21:42,436
Polnareff: Ah, man,
that’s unfortunate.

531
00:21:42,469 --> 00:21:45,372
Jotaro: Hmm? Oranges, huh?

532
00:21:45,405 --> 00:21:47,240
I was just getting thirsty.

533
00:21:47,274 --> 00:21:49,476
Think i’ll take one.

534
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:50,478
Polnareff: Huh?

535
00:21:50,511 --> 00:21:52,413
Joseph: What’s this?

536
00:21:52,446 --> 00:21:54,682
Polnareff: That man’s clothes...

537
00:21:54,715 --> 00:21:56,450
Jotaro: You recognize him?

538
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:59,286
Polnareff: Nope,
can’t say that I do.

539
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:04,057
Joseph: Right. Let’s go find out
how avdol and kakyoin are doing.

540
00:22:04,091 --> 00:22:05,626
Mondatta: "And so the brothers

541
00:22:05,659 --> 00:22:07,528
"eventually gave up
on their mission.

542
00:22:07,561 --> 00:22:11,298
"The battle was over, and after
all the chaos and the pain,

543
00:22:11,331 --> 00:22:13,934
jotaro and the others
were none the wiser."

544
00:22:13,967 --> 00:22:15,368
Brothers: Ba-dum-tss.

545
00:22:16,503 --> 00:22:19,606
♪

546
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:22,977
( Speaking and singing
in Japanese )

